Ukraine faces US ultimatum to accept a lopsided 'peace plan'
description: Donald Trump has given Kyiv until November 27 to agree to a proposed deal that heavily favors Russia. European leaders, confronted with a fait accompli, are striving to support Volodymyr Zelensky and put forward counterproposals.

description: The head of the Danish intelligence services allegedly provided false information to political leaders in the Kingdom of Denmark to justify placing the director of military intelligence under surveillance for nearly a year.

headline: Brazil's ex-leader Bolsonaro taken into custody over flight risk
description: Brazil's Supreme Court ordered the pre-emptive arrest of the former president on Saturday, after a judge said he was preparing to flee just days before starting his 27-year sentence for leading an attempted coup.

headline: The fall of Northvolt, Sweden's symbol of green reindustrialization
description: On March 12, the electric battery giant shut its doors for good. Nearly 5,000 people employed at the Skelleftea gigafactory lost their jobs. As the US-based company Lyten prepares to restart production, Northvolt's downfall has cast a chill over Sweden's ambitions to reindustrialize around clean technology.

headline: Trump's odd day: Enthralled by Socialist Zohran Mamdani and abandoned by MAGA lawmaker Marjorie Taylor Greene
description: The US president lavished praise on New York City's mayor-elect during a White House visit on Friday. Almost simultaneously, one of his most fervent allies announced her resignation from the House of Representatives, formalizing her break with the Republican leader.

description: Crude jokes, inappropriate stares and overt flirting are commonplace for women in service jobs where physical appearance is paramount. Employees remain poorly protected from this sexualization, which can amount to harassment.

headline: Activist Amine Kessaci: 'No, I will not stay silent. I will say and repeat that my brother Mehdi died for nothing. I will speak out about the violence of drug trafficking'
description: Known for his fight against the devastation caused by drug trafficking in the working-class neighborhoods of Marseille, the brother of Mehdi, aged 20, who was murdered on November 13, denounces 'the cowardice of those who order these crimes' and urges the French state to 'understand that a fight to the death is underway.'

headline: Nicolas Guillou, French ICC judge sanctioned by the US: 'You are effectively blacklisted by much of the world's banking system'
description: Six judges and three prosecutors at the International Criminal Court have been sanctioned by the Trump administration. In an interview with Le Monde, Guillou discusses the impact of these measures on his work and daily life.
